                    <BLOCKQUOTE><TABLE border="1"><TBODY><TR><TD>I thought that all the places of each "World" were one planet (Crux) Also, NT is on the same place as CP. AND CP is a barren canyon-world with oceans of maelstrom, and the only "Cities" there are are Point zeta and the monastery ruins.<BR /><BR />Sorry if I sound rude right now. Just wanted to correct something. </TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></BLOCKQUOTE><BR />I know that it's supposed to be that way in the game. But, you know how in the story Lego took the idea for LU? Well, they changed worlds and how everything is connected. So, every world is a planet. For example, FV is a chain of floating islands that span the entire planet, we only explore a very small portion in LU.<BR /><BR />-Formic<BR />-Milligan in game
                
            
			
				
			
			
